240
00:07:48,262 --> 00:07:50,631
- I decided to take the plunge.
- To apply for the show?

241
00:07:50,632 --> 00:07:52,471
- That's so cool.
- That's a good thing.

242
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:53,971
I didn't care if I failed.

243
00:07:53,972 --> 00:07:55,201
What about you, Witch with a Wok?

244
00:07:55,202 --> 00:07:57,101
- I...
- I'm sorry, but...

245
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:59,341
- You didn't have to do this.
- You weren't in a gang...

246
00:07:59,342 --> 00:08:00,971
You're not a real gangster wife, right?

247
00:08:00,972 --> 00:08:02,681
- Just let me talk.
- Okay, Witch with a Wok.

248
00:08:02,682 --> 00:08:04,011
I might forget. Let me talk.

249
00:08:04,012 --> 00:08:05,012
- Maybe her jacket doesn't fit her.
- You might forget?

250
00:08:05,013 --> 00:08:07,151
- I'll start over again.
- I'm uneasy being next to her.

251
00:08:07,152 --> 00:08:08,152
- She's so scary.
- Let me talk.

252
00:08:08,153 --> 00:08:09,482
All right. I'm sorry.

253
00:08:09,952 --> 00:08:13,552
- I'd worked in this field for long, - That was funny.

254
00:08:13,852 --> 00:08:14,952
but they didn't contact me.

255
00:08:15,492 --> 00:08:16,822
So I applied for the show.

256
00:08:17,022 --> 00:08:18,261
- Oh, really?
- By the way, how old are you?

257
00:08:18,262 --> 00:08:19,591
- You have a lot of experience?
- The two of us...

258
00:08:19,592 --> 00:08:20,861
I was born in 1980, the Year of the Monkey.

259
00:08:20,862 --> 00:08:21,901
Oh, you're the same age as me.

260
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:23,331
- Are you?
- Really?

261
00:08:23,332 --> 00:08:24,701
- I thought I was older than you.
- She looks younger than her age.

262
00:08:24,702 --> 00:08:26,331
- I thought I was older than you.
- She looks younger than her age.

263
00:08:26,332 --> 00:08:27,771
- She looks way younger than she is.
- Indeed.

264
00:08:27,772 --> 00:08:30,472
I ate a lot of jjajangmyeon, so I have smooth, silky skin.

265
00:08:30,972 --> 00:08:32,972
- She's older than me.
- Her comment is old-fashioned.

266
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:35,281
Her comment is old-fashioned.

267
00:08:35,282 --> 00:08:36,581
- She's around my age...
- That's good.

268
00:08:36,582 --> 00:08:37,881
- based on her comments.
- Her comment is very old-fashioned.

269
00:08:37,882 --> 00:08:39,481
- "Smooth, silky skin."
- Exactly.

270
00:08:39,482 --> 00:08:41,181
"I have smooth, silky skin?" That's so old-fashioned.

271
00:08:41,182 --> 00:08:42,721
- I like old-fashioned things.
- I see.

272
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:44,851
- Okay.
- Did you get cast, Hoon?

273
00:08:44,852 --> 00:08:48,291
As you know, I appeared on similar shows...

274
00:08:48,292 --> 00:08:49,421
- as a judge.
- That's right.

275
00:08:49,422 --> 00:08:52,361
I was offered to be in the first season.

276
00:08:52,362 --> 00:08:55,361
But I was in the US then.

277
00:08:55,362 --> 00:08:57,561
I refused to be on the show without knowing...

278
00:08:57,562 --> 00:09:00,371
I had no idea the show would be that successful.

279
00:09:00,372 --> 00:09:02,541
- Of course.
- So I waited...

280
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,671
- to be offered to be in Season Two.
- Right.

281
00:09:04,672 --> 00:09:05,971
But I didn't let anyone know.

282
00:09:05,972 --> 00:09:08,172
I got a call from Director Kim Hak Min.

283
00:09:08,982 --> 00:09:11,742
He asked if I could have a meeting about Season Two.

284
00:09:12,212 --> 00:09:14,211
I said I'd see him when I came to Korea.

285
00:09:14,212 --> 00:09:15,451
And we decided on the place to meet.

286
00:09:15,452 --> 00:09:16,881
- So I went to see the director.
- He must have suddenly left there.

287
00:09:16,882 --> 00:09:18,991
They did their research so well.

288
00:09:18,992 --> 00:09:20,791
I had never seen any directors or writers like them before.

289
00:09:20,792 --> 00:09:22,761
- I see.
- "Chef Song,"

290
00:09:22,762 --> 00:09:25,791
"don't you want to let more people know about pork?"

291
00:09:25,792 --> 00:09:28,961
"You can let people in the world know about pork through this show."

292
00:09:28,962 --> 00:09:30,731
- They already knew what I wanted.
- You could promote Korean pork?

293
00:09:30,732 --> 00:09:33,202
I've been running a barbecue restaurant to do so.

294
00:09:33,672 --> 00:09:36,041
- Right after he said that...
- You couldn't refuse the offer.

295
00:09:36,042 --> 00:09:38,401
They made it impossible for me to refuse.

296
00:09:38,402 --> 00:09:40,512
I made a call two weeks later...

297
00:09:41,242 --> 00:09:43,381
and said I'd be on the show as a contender.

298
00:09:43,382 --> 00:09:45,711
I said I'd do it even if I were a Black Spoon.

299
00:09:45,712 --> 00:09:47,951
- I accepted the offer.
- The writers of this show...

300
00:09:47,952 --> 00:09:49,821
found out everything about you including your childhood.

301
00:09:49,822 --> 00:09:52,292
- The writers are incredible.
- And then...

302
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:54,991
- The writers know everything, - They're thorough.

303
00:09:54,992 --> 00:09:57,361
- but they're refraining themselves.
- That's right.

304
00:09:57,362 --> 00:09:59,061
Hee Chul, you should be good to Hoon.

305
00:09:59,062 --> 00:10:00,161
- Don't be disrespectful to him.
- Okay.

306
00:10:00,162 --> 00:10:01,532
He was at the CIA when he was in the US.

307
00:10:02,002 --> 00:10:03,231
- What?
- Really?

308
00:10:03,232 --> 00:10:04,462
- The CIA...
- You mean, the culinary school?

309
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:07,032
- Slow down. They must be shocked.
- Okay.

310
00:10:07,502 --> 00:10:10,342
It's not an intelligence institution like the FBI.

311
00:10:10,502 --> 00:10:12,211
It just happens to have the same initials.

312
00:10:12,212 --> 00:10:14,672
It's the Culinary Institute of America.

313
00:10:15,042 --> 00:10:18,012
It's a culinary school in the US. It's a great school...

314
00:10:18,382 --> 00:10:19,611
when it comes to culinary arts.

315
00:10:19,612 --> 00:10:22,082
We had a lot of contenders from that school in this season.

316
00:10:22,652 --> 00:10:24,121
- I was so surprised.
- It's a famous school.

317
00:10:24,122 --> 00:10:25,692
- I entered the waiting room...
- About 20 contenders, I think.

318
00:10:25,952 --> 00:10:28,022
- About 20. More than that?
- I think there were more.

319
00:10:28,352 --> 00:10:29,421
- You didn't know who'd be there.
- We didn't know.

320
00:10:29,422 --> 00:10:32,162
Did you meet the other contenders at the first shoot?

321
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:33,991
- Yes, for the first time.
- Yes.

322
00:10:33,992 --> 00:10:35,632
- Really? You had no idea?
- We met for the first time.

323
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:38,432
Even when the contenders arrived in the morning,

324
00:10:38,602 --> 00:10:41,471
- we entered separately.
- Oh, really?

325
00:10:41,472 --> 00:10:43,602
- It was kept totally confidential.
- It was kept confidential.

326
00:10:44,072 --> 00:10:45,841
When we were in the waiting room,

327
00:10:45,842 --> 00:10:47,612
- we didn't know who would come.
- That's right.

328
00:10:47,672 --> 00:10:49,141
First, they separated...

329
00:10:49,142 --> 00:10:50,581
- the White and Black Spoons.
- That's right.

330
00:10:50,582 --> 00:10:51,642
We were in different buildings.

331
00:10:51,952 --> 00:10:53,551
- We didn't meet each other.
- And then they divided us...

332
00:10:53,552 --> 00:10:55,182
based on our ages.

333
00:10:55,422 --> 00:10:58,121
- The older ones were in the front.
- You were divided into groups.

334
00:10:58,122 --> 00:10:59,421
They were closest to the stairs.

335
00:10:59,422 --> 00:11:01,421
- So Chef Hou Deok Juk...
- Yes.

336
00:11:01,422 --> 00:11:03,821
- Sang Hyun was in that group.
- He was one of the older ones.

337
00:11:03,822 --> 00:11:05,332
Among all 100 contenders,

338
00:11:05,792 --> 00:11:07,892
- What was your age rank?
- I was the fourth oldest.

339
00:11:08,232 --> 00:11:11,262
- The fourth?
- I arrived before the others.

340
00:11:11,702 --> 00:11:13,531
When Chef Hou Deok Juk came in,

341
00:11:13,532 --> 00:11:14,771
- I was so surprised.
- That's natural.

342
00:11:14,772 --> 00:11:17,702
- He's almost 76.
- That's right.

343
00:11:17,872 --> 00:11:19,712
I was surprised that he participated in the contest.

344
00:11:20,212 --> 00:11:21,771
- I was really surprised.
- He's incredible.

345
00:11:21,772 --> 00:11:23,542
And there was another one who surprised me.

346
00:11:24,212 --> 00:11:25,312
- Who was it?
- Monk Seon Jae.

347
00:11:25,782 --> 00:11:28,752
- Oh, Monk Seon Jae.
- "A Buddhist monk in a contest?"

348
00:11:28,882 --> 00:11:30,251
As the curtain was going up,

349
00:11:30,252 --> 00:11:31,581
- she was behind the curtain.
- That's right.

350
00:11:31,582 --> 00:11:33,451
We saw a Buddhist monks' robe.

351
00:11:33,452 --> 00:11:35,291
- The others were wearing pants.
- When the curtain was going up?

352
00:11:35,292 --> 00:11:37,292
- But we saw a traditional robe.
- Right.

353
00:11:37,722 --> 00:11:39,262
- I have a question.
- The outfit itself was different.

354
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:42,261
Didn't you call other chefs...

355
00:11:42,262 --> 00:11:44,161
- to ask if they'd be there?
- Right.

356
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:46,032
No one told me.

357
00:11:46,102 --> 00:11:49,642
I entered the White Spoons' room. I was the last to go in.

358
00:11:49,972 --> 00:11:53,212
And I saw all the chefs who'd been on "Chef and My Fridge."

359
00:11:53,442 --> 00:11:54,471
- I was surprised.
- Right.

360
00:11:54,472 --> 00:11:56,011
- Chef Jung Ho Young, - Right.

361
00:11:56,012 --> 00:11:58,681
- Chef Sam Kim, Chef Raymon Kim, - Sam Kim.

362
00:11:58,682 --> 00:12:01,282
- and Chef Son Jeong Won.
- That's right.

363
00:12:01,652 --> 00:12:04,181
We didn't tell one another, so we were taken aback.

364
00:12:04,182 --> 00:12:05,182
We were all taken aback to see one another.

365
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:06,951
You promised not to talk about it when you signed the contract, yes?

366
00:12:06,952 --> 00:12:08,521
- It's a term in your contract.
- That's correct.

367
00:12:08,522 --> 00:12:10,161
- It was very...
- The penalty was 10,000 dollars.

368
00:12:10,162 --> 00:12:11,591
- Ten thousand dollars?
- The penalty was high.

369
00:12:11,592 --> 00:12:15,062
Jang Hoon would offer a million dollars for the information.

370
00:12:15,532 --> 00:12:17,262
- "Here."
- That's cool.

371
00:12:17,332 --> 00:12:19,632
- "Here are ten checks."
- That's so cool.

372
00:12:19,732 --> 00:12:21,671
"Who will be on the show? Oh, I see. Okay."

373
00:12:21,672 --> 00:12:23,601
- We had to pay money per case.
- He can't stand curiosity.

374
00:12:23,602 --> 00:12:25,141
He can't stand curiosity. And after a shoot, he'd say,

375
00:12:25,142 --> 00:12:27,341
- "Edit this part out."
- He has to know.

376
00:12:27,342 --> 00:12:29,012
(Edit this part out.)

377
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:31,081
- Each time we breached that term...
- He's cool.

378
00:12:31,082 --> 00:12:32,211
- Then...
- Yes?

379
00:12:32,212 --> 00:12:35,052
I heard they were preparing to shoot the third season.

380
00:12:35,452 --> 00:12:36,951
Are you interested in participating in it again?

381
00:12:36,952 --> 00:12:38,951
- You'll be a hidden White Spoon.
- I would do it.

382
00:12:38,952 --> 00:12:41,722
I didn't have the chance to show my culinary skills.

383
00:12:41,852 --> 00:12:43,961
- Right. All she did was...
- I was worse.

384
00:12:43,962 --> 00:12:46,191
I got eliminated in the first round. I failed really quickly.

385
00:12:46,192 --> 00:12:47,392
- You see...
- You should compete again.

386
00:12:47,492 --> 00:12:48,801
- I'll yield to you.
- I didn't know...

387
00:12:48,802 --> 00:12:50,101
Hoon was the pork master.

388
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,502
- He never even touched pork.
- He didn't get a chance.

389
00:12:52,702 --> 00:12:54,271
- I expected to cook pork.
- That's...

390
00:12:54,272 --> 00:12:56,572
- His pride is hurt.
- I think I could've done better.

391
00:12:56,702 --> 00:12:59,172
But I wouldn't compete in the contest again.

392
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:01,441
However, the contenders will compete as a team in the third season.

393
00:13:01,442 --> 00:13:02,682
Because it's a team match,

394
00:13:03,012 --> 00:13:06,012
some of my junior chefs who work at my restaurant...

395
00:13:06,352 --> 00:13:07,751
- want to compete in the contest.
- Will it be a team match?

396
00:13:07,752 --> 00:13:10,681
So I'll have to discuss with them before deciding.

397
00:13:10,682 --> 00:13:12,021
That means you want to do it.

398
00:13:12,022 --> 00:13:14,522
- He'll say to his junior chefs...
- "I'll give you a chance."

399
00:13:14,722 --> 00:13:15,761
I don't want to compete in the contest.

400
00:13:15,762 --> 00:13:17,461
- But in the third season...
- But I'd do it for my junior chefs.

401
00:13:17,462 --> 00:13:18,621
Brewmaster Yun, wouldn't you go on the show again?

402
00:13:18,622 --> 00:13:20,461
I work alone. I can't participate in it anyway.

403
00:13:20,462 --> 00:13:21,792
- Oh, right. She works alone.
- I wouldn't do it.

404
00:13:21,932 --> 00:13:23,802
- You need a team of 4.
- A 4-membered team.

405
00:13:23,902 --> 00:13:26,831
And you have to prove that all four of you have been working...

406
00:13:26,832 --> 00:13:28,071
- at the same restaurant.
- As employees.

407
00:13:28,072 --> 00:13:30,641
- Right.
- I run a one-man shop.

408
00:13:30,642 --> 00:13:32,542
In the third season...

409
00:13:32,772 --> 00:13:35,782
How about four of us forming a team to compete in it?

410
00:13:36,442 --> 00:13:37,442
Sang Min should be on the team.

411
00:13:37,443 --> 00:13:38,711
- Sang Min is a great cook.
- That's right.

412
00:13:38,712 --> 00:13:40,981
- Chef Kang from "Kang's Kitchen."
- "Kang's Kitchen?"

413
00:13:40,982 --> 00:13:42,482
- Chef Lee from "Kang's Kitchen."
- That's right.

414
00:13:42,882 --> 00:13:46,191
- My nickname could be Crazy Freak.
- That could be your nickname.

415
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:49,161
- The best sauce is a war of nerves.
- That could work.

416
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:50,622
- Right. I agree.
- That's right.

417
00:13:50,762 --> 00:13:52,531
When you met one another,

418
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:54,661
you didn't even say hello? How did that work?

419
00:13:54,662 --> 00:13:56,701
- Were you allowed to greet?
- Right. We didn't really...

420
00:13:56,702 --> 00:13:58,301
We greeted someone we knew.

421
00:13:58,302 --> 00:14:00,971
- Or... That's right.
- We just nodded to each other.

422
00:14:00,972 --> 00:14:03,101
- We just nodded to someone we knew.
- That's right.

423
00:14:03,102 --> 00:14:04,902
I was also like this. "You're a White Spoon?"

424
00:14:05,172 --> 00:14:06,211
"I'm a Black Spoon."

425
00:14:06,212 --> 00:14:08,512
- You said it to Chef Hou Deok Juk?
- I thought to myself.

426
00:14:09,012 --> 00:14:10,082
I didn't say that out loud.

427
00:14:10,582 --> 00:14:11,811
- Not Chef Hou Deok Juk...
- You saw Chef Hou and said,

428
00:14:11,812 --> 00:14:13,312
"Oh, you're here as a White Spoon?"

429
00:14:14,552 --> 00:14:16,351
- Not Chef Hou Deok Juk.
- It's understandable.

430
00:14:16,352 --> 00:14:18,181
She said such things to the other contenders.

431
00:14:18,182 --> 00:14:19,491
She was really scary.

432
00:14:19,492 --> 00:14:21,852
- How did you get along with CM?
- Because of my appearance?

433
00:14:22,222 --> 00:14:23,592
- You mean, Culinary Monster?
- Yes.

434
00:14:23,762 --> 00:14:25,991
That was the best war of nerves. He provoked Hoon.

435
00:14:25,992 --> 00:14:27,191
Exactly.

436
00:14:27,192 --> 00:14:29,032
He talked about your mentor to provoke you.

437
00:14:29,288 --> 00:14:32,428
That's right. Actually, I didn't know much about him.

438
00:14:32,629 --> 00:14:33,931
So some others told me...

439
00:14:33,932 --> 00:14:37,602
that he was the most popular chef among young people these days.

440
00:14:37,902 --> 00:14:40,572
He came forward when the 1-on-1 match began.

441
00:14:40,812 --> 00:14:44,142
- And he got on my nerves.
- Right.

442
00:14:44,242 --> 00:14:45,581
My first teacher was...

443
00:14:45,582 --> 00:14:48,012
Michael Anthony, the executive chef at Gramercy Tavern.

444
00:14:48,252 --> 00:14:49,882
And Culinary Monster had worked at that restaurant.

445
00:14:50,152 --> 00:14:53,552
He said Michael Anthony had said he was better than me.

446
00:14:54,052 --> 00:14:55,862
- Right.
- "That jerk."

447
00:14:57,622 --> 00:14:59,961
- He shouldn't swear here.
- He looked really angry.

448
00:14:59,962 --> 00:15:02,661
- Try not to be too angry. Be calm.
- He couldn't hide his emotion.

449
00:15:02,662 --> 00:15:06,072
- I know how you felt.
- It made even the viewers upset.

450
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,671
- Even the viewers got upset.
- My face turned red, right?

451
00:15:08,672 --> 00:15:09,742
- Yes.
- I...

452
00:15:10,072 --> 00:15:12,041
- The thought of it angers me again.
- It's natural for you to get upset.

453
00:15:12,042 --> 00:15:13,471
He's your junior by many years...

454
00:15:13,472 --> 00:15:15,171
- Michael Anthony was...
- By many years.

455
00:15:15,172 --> 00:15:18,682
the best mentor for me.

456
00:15:18,982 --> 00:15:21,582
As a mentor, he taught me everything.

457
00:15:22,052 --> 00:15:25,322
I couldn't believe he had said such a thing to Culinary Monster.

458
00:15:25,722 --> 00:15:26,821
- I was angry.
- Of course.

459
00:15:26,822 --> 00:15:30,161
- But everyone got excited.
- Right.

460
00:15:30,162 --> 00:15:31,861
So I couldn't just avoid competing against him.

461
00:15:31,862 --> 00:15:34,632
I would've looked weak if I didn't choose him.

462
00:15:35,192 --> 00:15:36,301
So I decided to have a match with him.

463
00:15:36,302 --> 00:15:38,001
- So was it because of your pride?
- That was one of the reasons.

464
00:15:38,002 --> 00:15:39,601
- That was a bad strategy.
- But he...

465
00:15:39,602 --> 00:15:40,931
provoked you intentionally to make you choose him.

466
00:15:40,932 --> 00:15:42,771
- He provoked me successfully.
- Culinary Monster.

467
00:15:42,772 --> 00:15:45,501
"I'll prove that what the teacher said is true."

468
00:15:45,502 --> 00:15:47,971
- Right. That's what he said.
- That's right.

469
00:15:47,972 --> 00:15:51,182
- In fact, his mentor never said it.
- Really?

470
00:15:51,442 --> 00:15:53,452
- Culinary Monster is a bad person.
- Right?

471
00:15:53,582 --> 00:15:54,681
- That's right.
- He never said it?

472
00:15:54,682 --> 00:15:55,952
- Did you talk to your mentor?
- Right.

473
