715
00:23:46,422 --> 00:23:47,722
in basketball.

716
00:23:48,252 --> 00:23:49,792
It wouldn't be an enjoyable game.

717
00:23:50,192 --> 00:23:52,792
- For real?
- Only one in the world.

718
00:23:53,092 --> 00:23:54,331
The one and only...

719
00:23:54,332 --> 00:23:55,962
- How would I lose?
- in the world.

720
00:23:56,432 --> 00:23:58,461
- Rather, Jang Hoon...
- My loss against my coach...

721
00:23:58,462 --> 00:24:00,031
in basketball is absurd.

722
00:24:00,032 --> 00:24:01,032
Jang Hoon would see it...

723
00:24:01,033 --> 00:24:02,631
as a golden chance.

724
00:24:02,632 --> 00:24:03,701
Some players are bigger...

725
00:24:03,702 --> 00:24:04,741
- than the team.
- Yes.

726
00:24:04,742 --> 00:24:06,072
- Correct.
- Bigger?

727
00:24:06,772 --> 00:24:09,071
Mun Jeong might not be happy about it,

728
00:24:09,072 --> 00:24:11,682
but she worked super hard during the team mission.

729
00:24:11,882 --> 00:24:13,011
She was really cool,

730
00:24:13,012 --> 00:24:15,012
- I agree.
- like a leader.

731
00:24:15,152 --> 00:24:17,551
So how did you feel when you lost?

732
00:24:17,552 --> 00:24:19,751
Even if it were a team mission,

733
00:24:19,752 --> 00:24:22,021
- it could crush you in an instant.
- You could blame the others.

734
00:24:22,022 --> 00:24:23,121
- Right?
- I didn't.

735
00:24:23,122 --> 00:24:24,491
- Or blame the judge.
- No.

736
00:24:24,492 --> 00:24:26,161
"What does Anh Sung Jae know?"

737
00:24:26,162 --> 00:24:27,191
It could've crossed your mind.

738
00:24:27,192 --> 00:24:28,331
- Of course.
- Right?

739
00:24:28,332 --> 00:24:29,731
- Totally.
- No, I swear it didn't.

740
00:24:29,732 --> 00:24:32,431
Why? Because I thought I'd advance.

741
00:24:32,432 --> 00:24:34,401
- I see.
- Right.

742
00:24:34,402 --> 00:24:37,241
- Either way, she'd advance.
- I took it lightly, okay?

743
00:24:37,242 --> 00:24:39,141
- She thought she'd advance.
- She's Seo Jang Hoon...

744
00:24:39,142 --> 00:24:40,771
- of the chef world.
- I had fun, okay?

745
00:24:40,772 --> 00:24:42,371
Chinese Cuisine Jang Hoon.

746
00:24:42,372 --> 00:24:44,441
- Correct. It was okay to lose.
- Chinese Cuisine Jang Hoon.

747
00:24:44,442 --> 00:24:46,212
- That was me.
- She and I...

748
00:24:46,452 --> 00:24:48,711
- are quite different.
- Is that so?

749
00:24:48,712 --> 00:24:50,052
You see, I...

750
00:24:50,082 --> 00:24:51,651
- What is it?
- You're very enthusiastic today.

751
00:24:51,652 --> 00:24:52,851
- You see, - Yes?

752
00:24:52,852 --> 00:24:56,161
I don't have reckless confidence like her.

753
00:24:56,162 --> 00:24:57,921
- Is that so?
- I've proved...

754
00:24:57,922 --> 00:25:00,892
that I was good enough since an early age.

755
00:25:02,832 --> 00:25:03,861
Always the best.

756
00:25:03,862 --> 00:25:05,262
- The only one in the world.
- It's...

757
00:25:05,662 --> 00:25:06,931
- True.
- Since my senior year...

758
00:25:06,932 --> 00:25:08,772
of high school,

759
00:25:09,172 --> 00:25:10,271
You've proven yourself.

760
00:25:10,272 --> 00:25:11,871
- I've proved myself.
- Mun Jeong has worked for 25 years.

761
00:25:11,872 --> 00:25:14,211
I won as soon as I got into college...

762
00:25:14,212 --> 00:25:16,041
and became the MVP.

763
00:25:16,042 --> 00:25:18,282
- Of course.
- No more words are needed.

764
00:25:18,382 --> 00:25:19,441
- Jang Hoon...
- But...

765
00:25:19,442 --> 00:25:21,682
didn't you win as a team back then?

766
00:25:21,852 --> 00:25:24,022
I played the biggest role in it.

767
00:25:25,222 --> 00:25:26,421
He has a share in it.

768
00:25:26,422 --> 00:25:28,451
- My share... No.
-True.

769
00:25:28,452 --> 00:25:31,221
- Jang Hoon did play a role.
- I have one of the largest shares.

770
00:25:31,222 --> 00:25:32,461
- That's why...
- Let's accept the truth.

771
00:25:32,462 --> 00:25:34,031
it's Yonsei of Seo Jang Hoon,

772
00:25:34,032 --> 00:25:35,931
not Seo Jang Hoon of Yonsei.

773
00:25:35,932 --> 00:25:37,662
- Wait. Back then, - Yes.

774
00:25:37,762 --> 00:25:39,502
that was the title of all the news articles.

775
00:25:39,772 --> 00:25:41,231
(Hee Chul is correct.)

776
00:25:41,232 --> 00:25:42,942
- Jang Hoon...
- It said, "Yonsei of..."

777
00:25:43,302 --> 00:25:45,671
Really. It wasn't Seo Jang Hoon of Yonsei.

778
00:25:45,672 --> 00:25:47,041
- Yonsei of Seo Jang Hoon.
- Yonsei of Seo Jang Hoon?

779
00:25:47,042 --> 00:25:48,541
- Jang Hoon is...
- For real.

780
00:25:48,542 --> 00:25:51,781
- Yonsei of Seo Jang Hoon.
- one in seven billion.

781
00:25:51,782 --> 00:25:53,012
- Then...
- Incredible.

782
00:25:53,052 --> 00:25:54,151
Na Ra...

783
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:55,411
- I'm most curious...
- I expected...

784
00:25:55,412 --> 00:25:56,681
- about her.
- Na Ra...

785
00:25:56,682 --> 00:25:58,882
to advance to the top rounds.

786
00:25:59,352 --> 00:26:00,591
- I did.
- Me too.

787
00:26:00,592 --> 00:26:02,721
From what I know,

788
00:26:02,722 --> 00:26:05,362
- don't we have to wait...
- Yes?

789
00:26:05,622 --> 00:26:07,191
three to four years to dine...

790
00:26:07,192 --> 00:26:09,431
at the restaurant you run?

791
00:26:09,432 --> 00:26:11,562
- The reservations...
- Waiting for four years is weird.

792
00:26:12,602 --> 00:26:14,602
Are you crazy? Can't you just go and eat there?

793
00:26:14,702 --> 00:26:16,171
- Why wait for four years?
- Isn't it...

794
00:26:16,172 --> 00:26:17,901
a fine dining restaurant?

795
00:26:17,902 --> 00:26:19,371
- It's weird, right?
- Totally.

796
00:26:19,372 --> 00:26:22,242
Does that mean we can't go there in the 2020s?

797
00:26:22,542 --> 00:26:24,341
- Must we wait until 2030?
- In 2030.

798
00:26:24,342 --> 00:26:25,511
- In 2030.
- What kind of place is it?

799
00:26:25,512 --> 00:26:26,651
It has to be 2030?

800
00:26:26,652 --> 00:26:28,211
- Is the address a secret?
- Listen.

801
00:26:28,212 --> 00:26:29,822
- In 2030?
- Her restaurant...

802
00:26:30,222 --> 00:26:32,322
- I disappear every now and then.
- The address...

803
00:26:32,552 --> 00:26:34,321
I get direct messages from all over the world.

804
00:26:34,322 --> 00:26:36,191
- From all over the world?
- That was what I meant.

805
00:26:36,192 --> 00:26:37,422
- So...
- To be frank,

806
00:26:37,792 --> 00:26:40,231
- the menu itself was ordinary.
- True.

807
00:26:40,232 --> 00:26:42,491
But why were you praised so highly?

808
00:26:42,492 --> 00:26:43,801
- What was your specialty?
- Was it the drinks?

809
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:45,702
I focused on the ingredients.

810
00:26:46,132 --> 00:26:47,671
- The raw ingredients?
- For example, dried pollack.

811
00:26:47,672 --> 00:26:49,771
I tried to communicate with the dried pollack.

812
00:26:49,772 --> 00:26:51,071
"Where are you from?"

813
00:26:51,072 --> 00:26:52,301
"Your ingredients..."

814
00:26:52,302 --> 00:26:53,871
- Did the dried pollack answer?
- "How should I cook..."

815
00:26:53,872 --> 00:26:55,211
- Yes.
- Something like,

816
00:26:55,212 --> 00:26:57,942
- "I'm from Noryangjin!"
- "How should I cook you?"

817
00:26:58,342 --> 00:27:00,111
- Did it answer?
- "Tteokbokki,"

818
00:27:00,112 --> 00:27:01,951
"why did you become rice cake?"

819
00:27:01,952 --> 00:27:03,452
Which answered you the most?

820
00:27:04,282 --> 00:27:06,081
- The dried pollack.
- The dried pollack did.

821
00:27:06,082 --> 00:27:07,351
- Did it?
- The dried pollack?

822
00:27:07,352 --> 00:27:08,892
- Was it the dried pollack?
- Seriously.

823
00:27:09,092 --> 00:27:10,591
- It came from the drying field.
- Exactly.

824
00:27:10,592 --> 00:27:12,691
Hoon should've also talked with the sea squirt.

825
00:27:12,692 --> 00:27:14,261
For real, I couldn't do that.

826
00:27:14,262 --> 00:27:15,831
- Right?
- The sea squirt didn't talk.

827
00:27:15,832 --> 00:27:18,862
Next is... This one kind of hurts to read out loud.

828
00:27:19,162 --> 00:27:21,471
Behind-the-scenes of "Culinary Class Wars 2..."

829
00:27:21,472 --> 00:27:22,702
is "elimination."

830
00:27:22,942 --> 00:27:25,201
As everyone...

831
00:27:25,202 --> 00:27:26,642
is a renowned chef,

832
00:27:26,872 --> 00:27:28,341
did you guess at which position...

833
00:27:28,342 --> 00:27:29,941
- Of course.
- you'd end up?

834
00:27:29,942 --> 00:27:30,942
- I'm sure they did.
- Did you?

835
00:27:30,943 --> 00:27:32,111
As for me,

836
00:27:32,112 --> 00:27:34,552
I thought, "Let's at least pass Round One."

837
00:27:35,252 --> 00:27:37,181
- It was 1 on 1.
- That was my goal.

838
00:27:37,182 --> 00:27:38,251
- Not win?
- Round One...

839
00:27:38,252 --> 00:27:39,521
- for the White Spoons was 1 on 1.
- Correct.

840
00:27:39,522 --> 00:27:40,821
As I was a White Spoon,

841
00:27:40,822 --> 00:27:43,361
it was 1 on 1 with 1 of the 20 Black Spoons who advanced.

842
00:27:43,362 --> 00:27:45,892
As long as I passed that match,

843
00:27:46,632 --> 00:27:48,331
- You'd be happy?
- I was happy with it.

844
00:27:48,332 --> 00:27:50,102
I bet Hoon wanted to advance to the top.

845
00:27:50,262 --> 00:27:52,031
No, I...

846
00:27:52,032 --> 00:27:53,131
Didn't you take part...

847
00:27:53,132 --> 00:27:54,271
- To win.
- expecting to get to the finals?

848
00:27:54,272 --> 00:27:58,272
When I met the other chefs in the waiting room,

849
00:27:58,372 --> 00:28:00,711
they gave me hope by saying,

850
00:28:00,712 --> 00:28:03,041
"I'm sure you'll win."

851
00:28:03,042 --> 00:28:04,211
- Obviously.
- They hyped you up.

852
00:28:04,212 --> 00:28:05,512
Even Chef Lee Geum Hee was like,

853
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:08,151
"You're here to win, right? I'm sure you'll win."

854
00:28:08,152 --> 00:28:09,821
With that, I expected...

855
00:28:09,822 --> 00:28:13,892
to rank in the top 4 or 5 at the least.

856
00:28:14,322 --> 00:28:16,191
But I got eliminated right away...

857
00:28:16,192 --> 00:28:17,621
- But the thing is...
- in the first round.

858
00:28:17,622 --> 00:28:19,861
Don't you have...

859
00:28:19,862 --> 00:28:21,962
- disciples, Hoon?
- I do.

860
00:28:22,092 --> 00:28:23,162
What did they say?

861
00:28:23,332 --> 00:28:24,402
What did they say?

862
00:28:25,302 --> 00:28:26,671
- This is interesting.
- How is that...

863
00:28:26,672 --> 00:28:29,572
- the first thing you ask me?
- "I knew it'd happen."

864
00:28:29,772 --> 00:28:31,001
- That hurt, right?
- What did they say?

865
00:28:31,002 --> 00:28:32,902
- He's on edge.
- "I knew it'd happen."

866
00:28:33,072 --> 00:28:35,271
Hoon, when you returned to the restaurant, were they like...

867
00:28:35,272 --> 00:28:37,181
(Disappointed)

868
00:28:37,182 --> 00:28:38,582
Because...

869
00:28:39,312 --> 00:28:40,781
(The disciples have changed.)

870
00:28:40,782 --> 00:28:42,452
I'm sure you get along with them.

871
00:28:42,682 --> 00:28:44,581
- Asking to do the dishes together.
- Yes.

872
00:28:44,582 --> 00:28:45,781
- I couldn't tell them...
- "Let's do the dishes."

873
00:28:45,782 --> 00:28:47,021
that I got eliminated,

874
00:28:47,022 --> 00:28:48,692
but I was at the restaurant.

875
00:28:49,122 --> 00:28:50,661
- At the restaurant?
- They assumed I got eliminated.

876
00:28:50,662 --> 00:28:53,162
- The disciples drew a conclusion.
- I didn't go out again.

877
00:28:53,292 --> 00:28:55,291
The atmosphere must've changed. At first, they must've been like,

878
00:28:55,292 --> 00:28:57,161
"I saw you on TV last night, Chef Song."

879
00:28:57,162 --> 00:28:59,262
But at one point, everyone would've been like...

880
00:28:59,532 --> 00:29:02,001
- Correct.
- Then...

881
00:29:02,002 --> 00:29:03,742
- Everyone was mindful. Kyung Hoon.
- Chef...

882
00:29:04,002 --> 00:29:05,841
- It's okay.
- Did no one...

883
00:29:05,842 --> 00:29:07,311
ask about the result?

884
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:08,312
- What?
- Questions like,

885
00:29:08,312 --> 00:29:09,312
"How's the contest going?"

886
00:29:09,313 --> 00:29:10,941
- Of course.
- So many asked.

887
00:29:10,942 --> 00:29:12,581
What did you say? You had to lie, right?

888
00:29:12,582 --> 00:29:14,552
- I couldn't say anything.
- Right.

889
00:29:15,512 --> 00:29:17,621
I simply couldn't say a thing.

890
00:29:17,622 --> 00:29:18,881
I had to pay 10,000 dollars...

891
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:20,121
- if I did.
- How upsetting.

892
00:29:20,122 --> 00:29:21,321
- It's a spoiler.
- Watch the show.

893
00:29:21,322 --> 00:29:22,391
- Exactly.
- Just watch the show.

894
00:29:22,392 --> 00:29:23,721
- Correct.
- Na Ra and Mun Jeong,

895
00:29:23,722 --> 00:29:25,221
what did you expect? Na Ra first.

896
00:29:25,222 --> 00:29:27,332
I didn't expect to pass Round One.

897
00:29:27,662 --> 00:29:30,231
- Little did I imagine becoming...
- Right.

898
00:29:30,232 --> 00:29:32,832
- one of the nineteen. For real.
- It's...

899
00:29:33,032 --> 00:29:34,072
As for me...

900
00:29:34,372 --> 00:29:36,941
- I bet she thought she'd win.
- No.

901
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:39,001
Rather than expecting to get into a certain rank...

902
00:29:39,002 --> 00:29:40,211
Be honest, okay?

903
00:29:40,212 --> 00:29:42,342
I wanted to get into the top eight.

904
00:29:42,472 --> 00:29:44,411
- Top 8?
- In the top 8...

905
00:29:44,412 --> 00:29:46,411
- I worked for the same place...
- Among 100?

906
00:29:46,412 --> 00:29:49,052
- for 25 years.
- Among 99.

907
00:29:49,752 --> 00:29:52,621
As I had to take part while bearing...

908
00:29:52,622 --> 00:29:56,521
- my career and all on my shoulders, - Top eight?

909
00:29:56,522 --> 00:29:57,522
- I thought...
- Top eight.

910
00:29:57,522 --> 00:29:58,522
"I should at least get in the top eight."

911
00:29:58,762 --> 00:30:00,861
That was my mindset. It didn't matter what place I got.

912
00:30:00,862 --> 00:30:02,761
I may look like a strong person,

913
00:30:02,762 --> 00:30:04,231
but I'm actually a very sensitive woman.

914
00:30:04,232 --> 00:30:06,131
- But you...
- What was that, all of a sudden?

915
00:30:06,132 --> 00:30:07,701
- All of a sudden?
- What's wrong with her?

916
00:30:07,702 --> 00:30:09,731
Why would you say that you're sensitive?

917
00:30:09,732 --> 00:30:12,041
- I don't know, either.
- What's wrong with her?

918
00:30:12,042 --> 00:30:14,841
What touched the viewers the most...

919
00:30:14,842 --> 00:30:17,481
was Chef Hou Deok Juk and Sang Hyun's part.

920
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:19,012
- Yes.
- That was...

921
00:30:19,542 --> 00:30:23,082
(Chun Sang Hyun, Eliminated)

922
00:30:23,482 --> 00:30:26,722
(The master and disciple hug each other after their struggles.)

923
00:30:28,792 --> 00:30:30,861
(I will...)

924
00:30:30,862 --> 00:30:32,821
(forever be...)

925
00:30:32,822 --> 00:30:34,561
(Master's disciple.)

926
00:30:34,562 --> 00:30:35,861
- That was so amazing.
- This was when...

927
00:30:35,862 --> 00:30:37,961
- I almost cried.
- It's like a movie.

928
00:30:37,962 --> 00:30:39,631
- That was really touching.
- To be honest,

929
00:30:39,632 --> 00:30:41,872
it has been 33 years.

930
00:30:42,332 --> 00:30:44,141
Since I first joined the company.

931
00:30:44,142 --> 00:30:47,611
And the one who shaped me to come this far,

932
00:30:47,612 --> 00:30:52,241
as a White Spoon, is Chef Hou.

933
00:30:52,242 --> 00:30:53,882
- He must be glad for you.
- So...

934
00:30:54,582 --> 00:30:58,382
That is why he will be my master forever.

935
00:30:58,652 --> 00:31:01,491
I'm sure you have the respect for him,

936
00:31:01,492 --> 00:31:04,992
but on the other side, you must have felt the barrier.

937
00:31:05,222 --> 00:31:08,031
Even as I was doing my own thing,

938
00:31:08,032 --> 00:31:09,692
I couldn't help but look over at him.

939
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:11,561
To see what he was doing. Why?

940
00:31:11,562 --> 00:31:13,402
There weren't many ingredients fit for Chinese cuisine.

941
00:31:14,102 --> 00:31:15,401
So I couldn't stop myself from looking over,

942
00:31:15,402 --> 00:31:17,402
and going over to have a taste.

943
00:31:17,572 --> 00:31:20,742
Still, his cooking was on another level.

944
00:31:20,842 --> 00:31:23,711
In the end, I lost, 2 against 0,

945
00:31:23,712 --> 00:31:25,142
but I felt completely at ease.

946
00:31:25,442 --> 00:31:26,982
I did the interview with a smile.

947
00:31:27,682 --> 00:31:29,382
(I am satisfied.)

948
00:31:29,882 --> 00:31:31,551
(He was happy, just being able to cook together.)

949
00:31:31,552 --> 00:31:33,292
But with Sang Hyun,

950
00:31:33,692 --> 00:31:36,392
leaving everything else aside,

951
00:31:36,662 --> 00:31:39,221
- I could just tell that he is...
- Yes.

952
00:31:39,222 --> 00:31:40,531
such a good-hearted person.

953
00:31:40,532 --> 00:31:42,061
- I can still feel it now.
- Yes.

954
00:31:42,062 --> 00:31:44,631
People can feel that,

955
00:31:44,632 --> 00:31:47,301
so that was why the last interview...

956
00:31:47,302 --> 00:31:50,942
- touched the viewers as well.
- Yes.

957
00:31:51,172 --> 00:31:54,112
You must have felt bad for being harsh on Coach Choi Hee Am.

958
00:31:54,512 --> 00:31:57,341
- No, that's not it.
- Why are you so...

959
00:31:57,342 --> 00:32:00,151
- That's nonsense.
- Jang Hoon may talk like this,

960
00:32:00,152 --> 00:32:01,211
but on the inside,

961
00:32:01,212 --> 00:32:03,851
